The Starting Strength program works if you follow it as prescribed, that's why we don't allow a lot of customization because novices typically don't make as fast progress if they customize things for themselves. While I believe that Mark Rippetoe's Starting Strength is a good program, this app is not a good representation of said program. It is not intutive and simple enough to use.   If I just finished my last set of squats, and I click the "next rep" button, why doesn't it take me to the next exercise? Why am I forced to click on the menu on top? Why do I have to tap the phone, to silence the countdown timer, once it hits 0? Why not just make it beep 3 or 5 times? Why do I always have to login again every time I turn on the app to backup my data? Why are there like 4 or 5 buttons on the workout screen, all of them with different options? The only thing on my workout screen should be my exercises (sets and reps), weights and a timer. All the extra options and settings, just keep them in a separate menu. Why does the app respond terribly to landscape mode? Why is there even a landscape mode, when it's not even needed in the first place?   Stronglifts is a complete ripoff of Starting Strength, but their app is simple and intuitive to use. That's a big reason why its such a successful app and you can't keep up with your competition with apps like these.  Keep it simple.

I'd love to track pull-ups, dips, or back extensions -- but I can't do it in the app!  Because of this, I really cannot recommend anyone use this app. Once you outgrow it, you'll be faced with either loosing your existing progress, trying to export and import into a different app (difficult), or using two methods of progress tracking. I'm fully satisfied with my purchase.

content: The best strength training app around. If it's worth having it's worth paying for. Leave the gimmicky nonsense apps and guides behind and embrace the barbell!

This app very good for the lifting of the weights.  The lifting of the weights is made much more convenience of the counting of the tracking.   The app helped me lift the dead thing from no dead thing to a 305 pound dead thing.  Now moving my uncle from the basement to the trunk of my car is made much easiness.

I would give this app 3.5 stars if possible, but I guess with 3, there's greater room for improvement.  Let's get one thing out of way: the knowledge imparted by the trainers (Rippetoe et al.) is top notch.  They are extremely knowledgeable with decades of experience and they've built a solid plan that can get you really strong in a very efficient manner.    That being said, this app has enough technical misses that make it something less than stellar.    The interface is mostly OK, but suffers from various annoying quirks.  For example, the countdown function is very clunky and will reset if you navigate to other parts of the app.  The separation between regular and warm up sets is also not intuitive and unnecessarily complicated.  Perhaps the most annoying thing though is the the app is surprisingly sluggish even on a relatively new phone (Galaxy S7 Edge).  There are noticeable lag times in almost every action.    This app will likely get most comparison to "5x5 StrongLifts" which at this time, is superior due to its much better performance and interface.  I believe the Rippetoe training method itself to be better though.  FWIW, this app does show promise.
replyContent: Thanks Kai, we're hoping with the coming update that many of those issues are resolved.  Hope you'll take another look at the app then.

content: The app works well, a does exactly what it says. It tracks your weight well, which is good becuase I like graphs, and seeing your progress visually is rewarding. The warm up calculator is easily the most useful feature of the program. Being able to customise the workout to different versions of SS would be good (for example, I wish I could select the Witchita Falls Novice Program). The only customisation available is to substitute Power Cleans in for the  Deadlifts in workout B.
replyContent: We're going to be adding in more programs in the update after next (1.14).  You can substitute power cleans for deadlifts now - on the settings screen click "Power Clean on Workout B" and this will allow you to choose power cleans.  If you click the 3 dots menu button, then you can switch power cleans for deadlifts in any workout.

content: Bug fix incoming
replyContent: Known bug, will be fixed in the next version. Thanks for the feedback.

content: You cannot alter the weight of the bar in the app, nor can you tell the app to ignore the bar weight.  [Edit]  Re your reply: App description doesn't state for 20kg only; it directly contradicts your reply to O.  Marsalek on 9/9 that "lowering the bar weight below Olympic barbell weight will be coming in an update this weekend"; and what about females who have to use a lighter bar? Very disappointing reply.
replyContent: It would be nice if you changed your review, given this feature is now in the app.

content: The interface of this app is laid out in an unintuitive fashion. The are no settings for adjusting bar and plate weights, or desired weight increase per workout. Explanations for exercises require Internet access to load, even for text.  There are better apps that give the logging and progression options out there, that you can adjust to the SS program. This was a waste of money.
replyContent: All of these are fixed in the latest update 1.13 which is available now.

content: I love the starting strength program, it's changed my life, the app is good but has bugs. I can't select the 4th or 5th sets on the power clean and my progress shows my deadlift going down, which it never has and I checked my history of workouts to see if I made an error, this wasn't the case. Also a rest timer would be great along with the ability to log chin-ups. The instructions and videos are great for reference as is the link to the forums, Please update and this will be five stars.
replyContent: All those things should be fixed in the current update 1.13.

content: Awesome for recording progress, calculating weights ect.   HOWEVER:  It won't let me complete the five sets for power cleans, I'm only able to select three of the five, which is extremely frustrating and causes it to go back to starting weight each time.  My gym-bro has the same issue, with an added issue of not being able to retro-actively adjust his progress chart, even after editing past workouts.   PLEASE FIX
replyContent: This is fixed in the current update 1.13.  Thanks for the feedback.

content: Works great!
Does the app allow you to log missed reps 5/5/4?  I've purchased the app but am reluctant to switch over yet from the app I'm currently using that allows for this function.
replyContent: Notes are now available to log missed reps.  Please update to 1.13.

content: Has all the features you need and they are well implemented. Very impressed.

I'm not new to lifting but I'm rather new to strength training so when I saw ss was a popular program I couldn't resist.I bought the book and relised I needed to keep a log but while researching bits and bobs online I noticed there was a release for an app..I had to have it.At first use it has all the makings off a great app/log The only question I have is  why do the warm up sets slightly differ from book?The app has 6 total and the book/forum recommend 5 ie 2x5 bar/40%/60%/80% ?
replyContent: Thanks Nick.  Warmup sets differ slightly for each exercise, Press and Deadlift have 5 warmup sets and the others have 6.  This was by design.

content: This has everything for anyone just starting. For those who have moved to intermediate the logs will not allow for more complexity but the resources are a perfect way to review what you should be doing while resting.
replyContent: Thanks Andres.  Intermediate logs are coming early next year.

content: I like the app, I had hoped that I could replace my training log book but it won't - I like to record warm up sets and assistance exercises. As others have said, it would be great to be able to record reps other than sets of 5, and also more than 3 sets. But for the rank novice the app is great. I did notice that the bar math calculator always seems to show the bar as 20 lbs but does show the correct plate loading. I really like the exercise instructions and videos - I like reading during rest intervals to
replyContent: Thanks Tom.  I haven't seen the "20lb" bar bug before.  There'll be a new update coming later this week, if you still see that bug can you please email me at hello@shabu.co and I will look into it further.  Thanks for your other feedback, its all being noted and we are thinking about expanding the training logs but nothing has been decided yet.

content: Been waiting for this app! Here is the list of what I think is important to have in the next update: 1) Warm up 2) Reps done 3) Advance Novice 4) Deadlift weight 10lb increment. Great apps!
It needs a rest timer, warm up calculator, and cloud sync, but it's a great start. Definitely worth it.
replyContent: Warmup Calculator and rest timer are both in the current update 1.13.  Please update your app.  Cloud sync will come next year.

content: Top app, everything i expexted it would be. Only hiccups that i cant add a weight with a decimal place, eg, 52.5kg,  which is annoying seeing as we progress in increments of 2.5. Other than that it's spot on.                       Edit: have sent the email to you.
replyContent: Please update your app Michael, this was fixed a long time ago.

content: Good and could be great however: 1. Every time you minimise the app, you have to refill in the details about previous exercises. This is quite a pain. 2. would be better if there was an option for barbell rows to replace cleans 3. Option to record reccomended aux. Exercises (pullups+dips).   N.b. I understand 2+3 are controversial however they are also quite popular!
replyContent: Minimise app / reload todays progression is fixed in the current update (1.13).  You can now use the notes section to add any information about assistance exercises, but we will be looking into making the exercise selection more flexible next year.

content: Is it possible for the app to keep track of the number of reps done? It's much easier to determine if you are progressing by comparing the number of reps done to the previous workout, especially when you start to plateau. Overall, I am really impressed with your app. 10/10 for now. 11/10 if you can keep track of reps
replyContent: Michael you can now use the notes function to count missed reps.  Please update to the latest version 1.13 which is available now.

content: Very nice initial launch! Clean and easy to use. The app feedback button doesn't seem to work, FYI. For future updates, I'd like to see: warm up sets calculations, ability to add additional/alternative lifts (i.e. chin-ups, back extensions, etc), and the ability to input past workouts.  (EDIT: Thanks for the clarification! I've added past workouts.)
replyContent: You can enter previous workouts in the "Training History" Section, press the "+" button in the bottom right hand corner.  We're looking into a more customisable training log at the moment but we are being careful about nto making the app too difficult to use for beginners.  Thanks for the feedback Andrew.

content: Could we also have the option of putting pendley rows in workout B? Am also not sure if we can input missed reps
replyContent: We're investigating a more customisable log now but we do want people to follow the program as prescribed in the book.

content: Money
Now all we need is the  milk consumption tracking app.
About time guys! This is sharp, clean, and easy. I've been waiting forever for this. Great job, reasonable price, and very useful for a very long time. Nice job!!! üòÇ
Perfect companion  for a beginner of the Starting Strength program or the more advanced individual who wants easy reference to the material during a workout.
Very handy companion for those already on the SS program. As another reviewer has said, warmup calcuator would be great.
replyContent: Warmup calculator is now available in the current update 1.13

content: Where is the warm up calculator?
replyContent: Warmup calculator is now available (as well as a lot of new features) in the current update 1.13

content: This app is a definite must have if you have the books!
